---
target: parser
version: 1
validations:
  - name: parser-package-exists
    type: file_check
    path: src/parser/parser.go
    contains:
      - "package parser"

  - name: frontmatter-parsing
    type: file_check
    path: src/parser/frontmatter.go
    contains:
      - "package parser"
      - "---"

  - name: intent-parser-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func.*ParseIntentFile" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validation-parser-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func.*ParseValidationFile" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: target-registry-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "type TargetRegistry struct" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-intent-schema-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func ValidateIntentSchema" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-project-intent-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func ValidateProjectIntent" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-validation-schema-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func ValidateValidationSchema" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: validate-all-specs-exists
    type: command_check
    command: grep -c "func ValidateAllSpecs" src/parser/*.go
    exit_code: 0

  - name: parser-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: go test ./src/parser/...
    exit_code: 0

  - name: parser-handles-missing-frontmatter
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Check the parser test files for test cases that verify:
      1. Files with no frontmatter (no --- delimiters) produce a clear error
      2. Files with missing required fields produce errors naming the missing field
      3. Files with invalid YAML produce errors with file path context
      4. Files with empty markdown body are accepted
      5. Validation files with unknown type values produce errors
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/parser/*_test.go"]

  - name: schema-validation-tests
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Check parser tests cover schema validation:
      1. ValidateIntentSchema catches missing name, missing version, invalid version
      2. ValidateProjectIntent rejects depends_on on project.ic
      3. ValidateValidationSchema catches missing target, invalid type, duplicate names
      4. ValidateAllSpecs walks intent/ and aggregates violations
      5. Cross-file validation catches name/directory mismatches
      6. Functions return []core.SchemaViolation (not just error)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/parser/*_test.go"]

  - name: parser-imports-only-core
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that the parser package only imports from:
      - Standard library packages
      - github.com/pboueri/intentc/src/core
      - Third-party YAML libraries (gopkg.in/yaml.v3 or similar)
      It must NOT import from other intentc packages (agent, builder, etc.)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/parser/*.go"]
---

# Parser Validations

These validations ensure the parser correctly handles YAML frontmatter extraction, schema validation, and target discovery. The schema validation functions (ValidateIntentSchema, ValidateProjectIntent, ValidateValidationSchema, ValidateAllSpecs) are critical for catching malformed spec files before builds proceed. Error messages are particularly important - a user with a malformed spec file should get clear, actionable feedback.
